            <scopecontent id="aspace_f747b112777d8426c6e14f77df04baa5">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Taintor Family Collection is made up of business, financial, and legal papers concerning various families of Branford and Guilford, Connecticut. The family names involved include Barker, Bishop, Foot, Fowler, Hill, Linsly, Monro, Rogers, Russell, Towner and Tyler. There seem to be no Taintor papers, although one document is annotated by a Charles M. Taintor (Yale 1900S). The papers were donated by Mrs. Hope Collins, of the Taintor Family, in May 1943.</p>
            </scopecontent>
